					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>A fragment of Judeo-Arabic commentary of Japheth ben Ali on Exodus 17:5-20:14.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb">Hebrew, Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="57v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Shemot</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש שמות</title>
							<note>
								<p>An Arabic translation of the Hebrew text is embodied, the first translated verse being Ex. 17:7 (folio 1v).</p>
								<p>Of the Hebrew text only the opening words of each verse are given.</p>
							</note>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="en">Japheth ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century </persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he">יפת בן עלי, הלוי</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex, square to semi-cursive script of approximately 15-16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex</support>
								<extent>57 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>202</height>
										<width>145</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>174</height>
										<width>110</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>57 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end)</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>6 quires (nos. 22-27), of mostly 10 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Quires signed with Hebrew letters on the righ-hand upper corner of the first page.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>The last quire is imperfect, the last three leaves having been lost.</p>
									<p>Several folios have been damaged and later restored on modern paper.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="24" writtenLines="24">
									<p>Visible pricking and ruling with a hard-point.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
